topic.title: CPU Subsystem Preface â€“ INTERNAL-ONLY NOTES

body.p: The following sections are customer facing HWS content for the CPU Subsystem. These sections deliberately exclude many internal details including the L1/L2 cache and L3 memory sizes, Cortex-A9 configuration options, references to internal-only peripherals that customers do not need visibility of (such as GDMA, PKT_CACHE, timers, Coresight, JTAG2AHB), and supported features presently selected to be not-customer-visible (such as SPI memory controller support for per-byte in-line ECC, and a second SPI memory controller chip select).
For a complete specification of the CPU Subsystem with all internal details, refer to the PM10_82_09_A CPU_G5 Subsystem TSB Engineering Document [ESC-2161036].
